                      <h5 class="mb-0">
                        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse-10" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne" class="d-block text-dark text-capitalize text-up-small font-weight-700">All you need to know about BITS GOA</a>
                      </h5>
                    </div>
                    <div id="collapse-10" class="collapse hide" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingOne">
                      <div class="card-block padding-30px">
                        <p class="text-justify"><i class="fa fa-star"></i> BITS Goa, which was founded in 2004, is a technical and science institute for higher education in India. The craze of experiencing college life in a place like Goa along with the great quality of curriculum and teaching methodology of BITS Goa is what makes a student desire a seat in this institution. The campus of BITS Goa is located in Zuarinagar, Goa, on the banks of the Zuari River. Around 2600 students reside in the campus. The campus of BITS Goa was listed as number 7 in the list of the most beautiful campuses in India by HolidayIQ.com. Situated in the surroundings of the bank of river Zuari, the campus boasts of a unique scenic beauty and panoramic view of waterways, forests, landscapes and hillocks.  The BITS Pilani K K Birla Goa Campus, is about 10 kms south of Vasco-da-Gama, 20 kms north of Margaon and 7 kms east of Goa Airport, along National Highway – 17B, Bypass road. The Campus houses the Main building, having academic and administrative offices, Guest House, Hostels for boys and girls, Student Activity Centre, faculty and staff quarters, Medical Centre, Playground and Shopping Complex. As far as sports facilities is concerned, BITS Goa encourages its students for active participation in different sports and for the same along with a common playground and courts for Basketball, Tennis and Badminton, BITS Goa Campus has a BCCI-recognized cricket ground maintained by the Goa Cricket Association that has hosted several national level tournaments such as the Vijay Hazare Trophy and a football ground maintained by Salgaocar F.C.</p>
                        <p class="text-justify"><i class="fa fa-star"></i> <i class="fa fa-star"></i> Academics: The academic course structure of BITS Goa is governed by the university of BITS Pilani. However, each campus has its own autonomous administration, student welfare division, faculty recruitment and placement division. Being an autonomous institute, students also have options of other programs apart from the ones they are admitted in. This may be done by aid of various systems.</p>
                        <p class="text-justify"><i class="fa fa-star"></i> <i class="fa fa-star"></i> Dual Degree System: BITS Pilani, Goa Campus offers a dual degree to the students of Master of Science programs. Under the dual degree scheme, a student is offered two separate degrees on graduation : a degree in Master of Science (Hons.) and in Bachelor of Engineering (Hons.) However, the program increases the duration of his/her stay on campus by at least two semesters. The compulsory disciplinary courses of the second program are completed in the seventh and eighth semesters. The final year (ninth and tenth semester) is dedicated for two, semester long, off campus industrial training internships or master’s thesis.</p>
                        <p class="text-justify"><i class="fa fa-star"></i> <i class="fa fa-star"></i> Program Transfer: BITS Goa also offers flexibility in opting for other courses or to transfer from one program to another at the end of first year, if the student has performed well in academics.</p>
                        <p class="text-justify"><i class="fa fa-globe"></i> If the student is in the top 10 among full batch of students of the campus in terms of CGPA after their first year, then it is allowed for the student to take a B.E. + B.E. dual degree.</p>
                        <p class="text-justify"><i class="fa fa-globe"></i> If the student is in the top 30 students of the campus in terms of CGPA after their first year, one can abandon their degree for another, i.e. transfer from one program to another. BITS Goa also gives due importance to Humanities and Arts and it is mandatory for a student to take at least three humanity courses in total.</p>
